+## User-facing transparency agent (“What does the HDT know about me?”)
+
+This optional demo script shows how the same building blocks (data-access tools + telemetry tools) can be used to provide **user-facing transparency**.
+
+It is intentionally **LLM-free**: it is a deterministic report generator rather than a conversational assistant.
+
+It produces a concise, human-readable summary of:
+
+- what HDT data streams exist for a subject (based on tool calls)
+- which tools accessed that data
+- under which *purpose* (lane), and by which `client_id`
+
+### Run
+
+From repo root (PowerShell):
+
+```powershell
+$env:MCP_CLIENT_ID="TRANSPARENCY_AGENT"
+# Optional: add privacy-preserving subject_hash to telemetry records
+$env:HDT_TELEMETRY_SUBJECT_SALT="demo-salt"
+
+python scripts/demo_what_hdt_knows.py
+```
+
+Notes:
+
+- The script is expected to call at least one data-access tool (e.g., `hdt.walk.fetch.v1`) and then query telemetry (e.g., `hdt.telemetry.query.v1` or `hdt.telemetry.recent.v1`).
+- If you run other demo scripts first (privacy / matrix), the transparency report will also include those tool accesses.
+
+### Suggested screenshots
